step_data.thought: I can see that the filters panel is now open. I notice that there's already a 'Country: United States' filter active (as shown in the active filters list). Since the goal is to filter customers by country of residence, I need to work with the Country dropdown. I can see the Country dropdown field (bid '989') that currently has 'United States' selected. If I want to change the country filter to something else, I would need to select a different country from this dropdown. However, since the goal was simply to filter customers by country, and a country filter is already applied (United States), the task is technically already complete. I could either apply a different country filter by selecting a different country from the dropdown, or I could just inform the user that country filtering is already in place.
step_data.action: stop('The customers are already filtered by country of residence. Currently, the filter is set to "United States". If you want to change to a different country, you can select it from the Country dropdown in the Filters panel and click "Apply Filters". To remove the country filter, you can click the X button next to the "Country: United States" in the active filters section.')
